race.comment: ALPINE FURY (2) resumes and is a promising gelding coming off a near miss and a 5L Maiden win, both at this track. Has the inside gate and will be naturally improved. Has trialled twice and is the one to beat. GEORGARONI (1) won his Maiden here on debut as expected and was immediately tipped out. Resumes owning a Longford trial win and Pires sticks. A bold return is on the cards. THE PIRATE QUEEN (8) was too good for a Maiden field when resuming over 1220m at Launceston. Maps well and stripping fitter she should be right in it. SMIFFY (9) resumes and would be a hope if presented forward this time around. The wide gate makes it tougher.
